# Configuration Management

## ConfigOverride.xcconfig Usage
- Use ConfigOverride.xcconfig for all app settings instead of hardcoding in Info.plist
- Required settings: APP_DISPLAY_NAME, APP_VERSION, APP_BUILD_NUMBER, DEVELOPER_TEAM, BUNDLE_IDENTIFIER, APP_GROUP_ID
- Never hardcode sensitive data in configuration files
- Use environment-specific configurations when needed

## Bundle Configuration
- Bundle version and build number must come from ConfigOverride.xcconfig
- App display name should be configurable via xcconfig
- Developer team and bundle identifier must be externalized
- App group ID should be configurable for different environments

## Security
- Never store API keys, secrets, or sensitive data in configuration files
- Use Keychain for sensitive configuration data
- Validate configuration values at runtime
- Provide meaningful error messages for configuration issues

## Best Practices
- Keep configuration files version controlled
- Document all configuration options
- Use meaningful names for configuration keys
- Provide default values where appropriate
- Validate configuration on app startup